<h3 class="mega align-center" id="xui-breakpoint-shortcodes">breakpoint shortcodes</h3>
<div data-grid>
  <div data-col="2">
    <div class="h1 align-center ink-link">xs</div>
  </div>
  <div data-col="2">
    <div class="h1 align-center">sm</div>
  </div>
  <div data-col="2">
    <div class="h1 align-center">md</div>
  </div>
  <div data-col="2">
    <div class="h1 align-center">lg</div>
  </div>
  <div data-col="2">
    <div class="h1 align-center">xl</div>
  </div>
  <div data-col="2">
    <div class="h1 align-center">xxl</div>
  </div>
</div>
<div class="spacer"></div>
<table class="table">
  <tr>
    <td><em>empty</em></td>
    <td>for all sizes - should be used in <span class="code">data-col</span> instead of <em>xs</em>.
    </td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td><span class="code">xs</span></td>
    <td>mobile: <em>[0]</em> up or from <em>[0]</em> up to <em>[479px]</em></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td><span class="code">sm</span></td>
    <td>mobile landscape: <em>[480px]</em> up or from <em>[480px]</em> up to
      <em>[719px]</em></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td><span class="code">md</span></td>
    <td>tablet: <em>[720px]</em> up or from <em>[720px]</em> up to <em>[1023px]</em></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td><span class="code">lg</span></td>
    <td>tablet landscape: <em>[1024px]</em> up or from <em>[1024px]</em> up to
      <em>[1279px]</em></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td><span class="code">xl</span></td>
    <td>desktop: <em>[1280px]</em> up or from <em>[1280px]</em> up to <em>[1919]</em></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td><span class="code">xxl</span></td>
    <td>widescreen: <em>[1920px]</em> up.</td>
  </tr>
</table>

<p>breakpoint shortcodes can post-fixed to most of classes or attribute-values. normally it
  means that the style takes effect from the breakpoint up. A few styles just use a specific
  <strong>breakpoint area</strong> (e.g. from xs to xs-max).</p>

